1
00:00:05,967 --> 00:00:08,667
<i>I fight for this family
in ways you don't see.</i>

2
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,933
<i>If you're pushing me away,
too...</i>

3
00:00:11,067 --> 00:00:12,200
<i> where does that leave me?</i>

4
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,800
<i>No matter what I do, it's like
I'm always being watched.</i>

5
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:15,967
<i> Cut me some slack.</i>

6
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:17,167
<i> I'll try.</i>

7
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:20,367
<i>I don't want to be the reason
you're unhappy.</i>

8
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,033
<i> Surprise! Happy birthday!</i>

9
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:23,967
<i> Make a wish.</i>

10
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:25,700
<i> I really hope you can come.</i>

11
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,333
<i> Jasmine!</i>

12
00:00:27,467 --> 00:00:28,133
<i> Ash!</i>

13
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,267
<i>Hey, Ash, where are Uncle
and Aunt?</i>

14
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> Hi, Marj!</i>

15
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> Did you guys miss us?</i>

16
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:37,433
<i> Sorry, Uncle.</i>

17
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:38,400
<i> Sorry.</i>

18
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:40,167
<i>Why are you looking at me
like that?</i>

19
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,333
<i>I'm noticing something
in the air.</i>

20
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:41,867
<i> It's like...</i>

21
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,100
<i> there's tension.</i>

22
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:45,133
<i>Don't you ever get tired
of playing games like that?</i>

23
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>I'm sure you miss your daughter,
too.</i>

24
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:48,633
<i> Thea, don't.</i>

25
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,533
<i> What's going on?</i>

26
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:52,267
<i> Are you guys fighting?</i>

27
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:57,367
Hon...

28
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:58,367
no.

29
00:00:59,767 --> 00:01:05,133
Paolo's just panicking because
his client's being difficult.

30
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,567
Right, Pao?

31
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,133
He was just telling me
about all the challenges

32
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:11,100
at Torrecampo Realty.

33
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:14,300
Guess I triggered something.

34
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:19,767
Yeah, some people just know
how to push your buttons.

35
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,933
That's why I'm getting heated.

36
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:23,800
I thought it was something
serious.

37
00:01:28,267 --> 00:01:33,300
Anyway, I'm going to go look
for my husband and daughter.

38
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:36,133
They're probably with
the grandparents.

39
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,033
I'll see you around.

40
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:46,900
I've already given
Jasmine her medicine.

41
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:48,533
<i> How are you?</i>

42
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,100
I miss you. How are you?

43
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:52,233
I'm just here at the bar.

44
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,400
Well, don't drink too much.

45
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:57,100
It's just a little.
You want some?

46
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:58,233
Just a little.

47
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:52,300
<i>Why can't you at least try
to mingle with your dad?</i>

48
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:54,733
<i>You're like a ghost
at the party.</i>

49
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:57,000
Because we're not exactly
thrilled to see each other.

50
00:02:57,133 --> 00:02:58,500
It's always been like that.

51
00:02:58,633 --> 00:03:00,267
I don't need to pretend anymore.

52
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:04,900
Edward, it's been 16 years.

53
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:07,667
Move on from your anger toward
your father.

54
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:15,067
What, don't you want to get any
inheritance when he's gone?

55
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,200
Is that all that matters to you?

56
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:19,333
I'm thinking about our child's
future!

57
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:24,933
Mom, Dad, please.
Can you not argue?

58
00:03:25,067 --> 00:03:28,367
You, too! Where have you been?

59
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,700
Didn't I tell you to stay glued

60
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,900
to your grandmother
and grandfather all night?

61
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:35,767
And tell them how much
you miss them?

62
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,433
But you keep disappearing.

63
00:03:37,567 --> 00:03:38,933
Where do you keep
sneaking off to?

64
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:42,300
I...

65
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:44,400
I was with Jasmine.

66
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:46,033
Exactly!

67
00:03:46,167 --> 00:03:49,933
This is your chance
to bond with them.

68
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:52,067
Do you want them to be closer
to Jasmine than you?

69
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,033
Thea, that's enough.

70
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:56,600
Ashley, come on.
We're only here once in a while.

71
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:58,733
Take this opportunity, okay?

72
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:03,767
We're not just here because
it's Jasmine's birthday, okay?

73
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:06,967
You have this whole weekend
to show your grandparents

74
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:10,733
you're the best granddaughter
they have.

75
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:11,433
Got it?

76
00:04:11,567 --> 00:04:13,400
Stop pressuring our daughter.

77
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:15,467
She doesn't have to try so hard.

78
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,900
There's nothing wrong
with just being herself.

79
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:20,000
Don't compare her to you!

80
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,367
Ash,

81
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,633
go to your room.

82
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:27,933
Excuse me.

83
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:55,167
-Can I come in?
-Hurry. Come in.

84
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,633
You've still got a few minutes.

85
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,967
Happy birthday!

86
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:10,267
How are you?

87
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:13,933
Ash, this is seriously
the best birthday ever.

88
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:15,967
And the best gift?

89
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:18,633
Mom said she's going
to trust me more.

90
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:22,400
And dad said they're going
to fix things.

91
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:24,267
That they'll make things better.

92
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,667
For the first time...

93
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:28,833
I can breathe.

94
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:31,067
Like, finally.

95
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:35,867
You know, Jas,

96
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,667
even when you guys have issues,

97
00:05:41,067 --> 00:05:45,300
even when you and your mom
fight sometimes,

98
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,567
you're still better off.

99
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:52,533
Ash.

100
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:58,600
Why does that sound personal?

101
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,400
It's not.

102
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:03,000
It's nothing.

103
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:04,767
I'm just really happy for you.

104
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,533
Ash, this isn't just an online
video call

105
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,467
where you can turn
your camera off.

106
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,333
I can sense it.

107
00:06:12,633 --> 00:06:13,733
Something's different.

108
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:16,867
Because...

109
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:22,733
even when you guys fight,

110
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,967
you still have that thing, Jas.

111
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:32,167
That moment where someone says,
"Let's fix this."

112
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:35,633
Someone's making an effort.

113
00:06:36,733 --> 00:06:38,533
Someone's trying.

114
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:40,567
Ash, what is it?

115
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,667
I'm sorry.

116
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:44,467
I'm sorry, Jas.

117
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,800
Let's breathe, okay?

118
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,967
Ready?

119
00:06:57,233 --> 00:07:01,667
One, two, three...

120
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,833
I'm sorry.

121
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:05,333
I'm sorry, I can't do this
right now, Jas.

122
00:07:08,267 --> 00:07:11,400
I might just cry harder.

123
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:13,400
Then cry.

124
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,133
I mean, come on.

125
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:18,833
Cousins. Best friends.
Partners in crime.

126
00:07:19,133 --> 00:07:21,267
I won't push you about
what's going on.

127
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:25,100
Here.

128
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,700
No judgment.

129
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:30,200
Just let it out.

130
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:33,233
I'm here.

131
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,767
Love?

132
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:09,733
You okay?

133
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,967
Yeah. It's just hot in here.

134
00:08:16,567 --> 00:08:17,533
Edward,

135
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,533
how's your business in Cebu?

136
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:26,200
Torre Tech Solutions?

137
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:30,067
Thea says it's growing.

138
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:35,900
It's okay. Steady, Dad.

139
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,733
And Ashley's at the top
of her class in Math.

140
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:47,200
She even won the Science Fair
last month.

141
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:53,033
And her grades last quarter?
Straight A's on her report card.

142
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,633
- Wow!
- Again.

143
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:59,433
See? I knew it.
My granddaughter's brilliant.

144
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:02,600
Thank you.

145
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:05,700
Congratulations, Ashley.
That's not easy.

146
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:10,200
And not just academics.

147
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,433
She's also a varsity
in badminton.

148
00:09:13,467 --> 00:09:16,500
She even volunteers at her club.

149
00:09:16,633 --> 00:09:20,567
Wow, right?
Ashley's so multitalented.

150
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:24,933
Total overachiever.

151
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,300
That's wonderful, Ashley.

152
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:35,300
Jasmine, why don't you try
sports next school year?

153
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:41,000
Well, that's a Torrecampo
for you.

154
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:44,300
Talent clearly runs
in the family.

155
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,467
Of course.

156
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,333
She takes after her dad.

157
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:13,433
Dad,

158
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:19,467
you don't have to be sarcastic.

159
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,100
Like you'd actually believe

160
00:10:21,233 --> 00:10:23,867
Ashley got her achievements
from me.

161
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:26,933
I admit.

162
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:29,633
Paolo's better than me
at pretty much everything.

163
00:10:29,767 --> 00:10:31,700
I've accepted that.

164
00:10:31,933 --> 00:10:35,133
But that doesn't mean
I'm worthless.

165
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:36,567
That I don't matter.

166
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,367
I'm a good person.

167
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,900
I work hard.

168
00:10:42,033 --> 00:10:43,167
I don't quit.

169
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:48,000
And that's what Ashley got
from me, right?

170
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,733
Hard work. And heart.

171
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:58,667
Let's not ruin lunch
over little things.

172
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,433
Come on, the food's ready.

173
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:05,900
Ashley, Jasmine.
This is really good.

174
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,833
You should try it.

175
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:12,333
And the grilled squid? So good.
So let's all eat now.

176
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,300
We've got roast beef,
grilled squid, and vegetables.

177
00:11:14,433 --> 00:11:16,067
Come on, let's eat.

178
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,400
No, thanks.

179
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:29,733
<i>Yolly, what happened at lunch
earlier was intense.</i>

180
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:33,367
I thought Sir Edward
and Sir Greg were okay now?

181
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,733
The crack between those two
runs deep.

182
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:42,733
You can't just patch that up.

183
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:47,133
But haven't they seemed fine
lately?

184
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:50,500
In front of other people, yeah.

185
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:53,000
But when it's just the two
of them?

186
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,367
They slip.

187
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,400
They hurt each other so easily.

188
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:01,800
You know what I'm scared of?

189
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:05,633
One more mistake from Sir Edward

190
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:08,967
and it's war again between him
and his father.

191
00:12:10,233 --> 00:12:14,567
I hope the tension's gone.

192
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,233
The kids saw everything earlier.

193
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,567
Yeah.

194
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:21,267
And when the kids
get dragged into it,

195
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,167
the family wounds
just cut deeper.

196
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:40,133
Love?

197
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:43,433
Since it's school break,

198
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:47,667
I was thinking of talking
to Thea and Edward.

199
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,233
If they're heading back to Cebu
after this weekend,

200
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:53,500
maybe Ashley could stay here
for a while.

201
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:55,600
Why?

202
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:57,167
Why not?

203
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,933
At least Jasmine would have
someone her age

204
00:12:59,067 --> 00:12:59,800
to hang out with.

205
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:02,233
She wouldn't have to sneak
around.

206
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:04,233
The kids would be happy.

207
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:09,000
Maybe not right now, Love.

208
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:10,567
Love...

209
00:13:11,033 --> 00:13:12,667
When, then?

210
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:15,433
We're always planning
the cousins' vacations,

211
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:18,033
but they never happen.

212
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:20,900
Ashley is Jasmine's cousin,
Love.

213
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,967
She's your brother's daughter.

214
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:29,567
It's not that
I don't want her here.

215
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:31,000
I just want...

216
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:34,300
family time.

217
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:36,467
Just us.

218
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:40,800
Didn't we say we'd focus more
on each other?

219
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:43,967
Love,

220
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:49,800
why don't you want Ashley
to be with our daughter?

221
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:52,167
She's family, too.

222
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:56,100
Our daughter would be even
happier if they were together.

223
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:01,133
And I trust Ashley with Jasmine.

224
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:06,533
You know, we'd even get
more time for ourselves.

225
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:15,033
Maybe Edward already has plans
for his family this summer.

226
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:20,700
Why are you so against Ashley
staying here?

227
00:14:22,667 --> 00:14:25,367
Do you have an issue with them?

228
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,700
With the kid?

229
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:27,700
No.

230
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,700
What are you talking about?

231
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:33,567
Maybe we should ask Edward first
if they have plans this summer.

232
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,733
I just don't want us deciding
on our own.

233
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,933
Take that up to my room.

234
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:25,700
Hurry up!

235
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:27,333
Be careful with those!

236
00:15:27,467 --> 00:15:28,633
Because they're...

237
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,633
heavy.

238
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:34,800
Careful on the stairs.

239
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,267
Hi, Marj.

240
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,900
Oh, you're still up.

241
00:15:38,033 --> 00:15:39,800
Sorry about the noise.

242
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:41,867
I did a lot of shopping.

243
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,600
Wow, that's a lot.

244
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,267
For Ashley.

245
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:49,333
We're planning a family outing.
You know, matching outfits.

246
00:15:49,467 --> 00:15:52,733
Maybe out of the country.
Or out of town.

247
00:15:52,867 --> 00:15:54,733
We're still deciding.

248
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:59,000
Honestly, we feel so blessed
right now.

249
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:01,700
Edward's company is doing
really well.

250
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:03,867
So, you know...

251
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,767
we can kind of do what we want.

252
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:08,533
Must be nice.

253
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:13,000
With Jasmine and me,
even if we want to travel,

254
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:16,167
I can't help but worry.

255
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,733
What if it affects her health?

256
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:20,800
So even if we want to...

257
00:16:22,267 --> 00:16:24,633
it still feels risky.

258
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:30,933
Oh my gosh, Marj, I'm sorry.

259
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:34,000
That sounded insensitive.

260
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:38,833
I didn't mean to rub in
how happy and blessed we are.

261
00:16:40,233 --> 00:16:43,367
I know your exhaustion
is on another level.

262
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:46,400
Jasmine's situation
is different.

263
00:16:46,667 --> 00:16:50,133
Not something normal families
could handle.

264
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:53,133
Yeah.

265
00:16:53,467 --> 00:16:54,467
It is different.

266
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,867
That's why we're trying,
little by little,

267
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,600
to find new ways to bond
as a family.

268
00:17:03,533 --> 00:17:07,233
Well, good night, Marj.

269
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:09,633
I hope it works out.

270
00:17:09,767 --> 00:17:10,600
You know...

271
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:13,133
your setup's a little
challenging.

272
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,933
Okay, I'm heading in.

273
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:36,733
Mom, can we do this tomorrow?
We still have tomorrow.

274
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:37,967
No!

275
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,633
Try this on now!

276
00:17:39,867 --> 00:17:40,400
So we know what looks good
on you.

277
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:43,200
We still have tomorrow...

278
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:44,867
Put it on.

279
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:48,467
Honey, all of this is for you.

280
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:50,867
So you'll always look pretty
like your mom.

281
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,733
Always presentable.

282
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:55,600
So your grandparents
will adore you even more.

283
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:58,700
Here, this one's nice. Wait.
I will find the top.

284
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:00,467
Thea,

285
00:18:01,933 --> 00:18:04,600
I really think we should start
watching our expenses.

286
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:08,500
What now?

287
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:11,800
Do you want Jasmine
to outshine Ashley

288
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,467
like what happened with you
and Paolo before?

289
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:16,867
Just because we have a business

290
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,233
doesn't mean we should spend
like crazy.

291
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,200
And why not?

292
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,333
That's what money's for, right?

293
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,767
To spend.

294
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:26,867
Unless...

295
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,567
we need to start saving.

296
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,967
Is there something you're not
telling me?

297
00:18:37,967 --> 00:18:39,733
No.

298
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:40,800
It's not like that.

299
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:43,667
I just don't want you
stressing over numbers

300
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,833
while we're on vacation.

301
00:18:45,967 --> 00:18:48,667
I just want us to be smart
with our money, that's all.

302
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,933
Okay. Noted.

303
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:54,500
But that doesn't mean we have
to live like we're poor

304
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:56,867
just to be smart, right?

305
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,733
This one's nice.

306
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:02,767
This.

307
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:03,933
It's pretty.

308
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:07,000
The color works.

309
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:08,733
Or something colorful?

310
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:09,933
It's okay.

311
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:16,067
Ashley, where are you?

312
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,567
I'm already at the restaurant.
Hurry up!

313
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,000
I hate it when you keep me
waiting.

314
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:37,100
Hashtag blessed.

315
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:42,300
Die of envy, everyone.

316
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:48,967
Mr. Vergara?

317
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,767
Mr. Vergara.

318
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:05,800
It's me.

319
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:07,467
Thea.

320
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:10,967
Edward Torrecampo's wife.

321
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:15,200
Your business partner
at Torre Tech Solutions.

322
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,567
Of course, I remember you, Thea.

323
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:20,300
But business partner?

324
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:24,033
I haven't been Edward's partner
in almost two years.

325
00:20:26,733 --> 00:20:28,367
Wait.

326
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:31,400
What do you mean the business
is going under?

327
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:34,300
Son, you told me you were moving
to Cebu to thrive.

328
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,867
To build your legacy.
To prove yourself.

329
00:20:37,033 --> 00:20:39,533
What kind of plot twist is this?
What is going on?

330
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:41,633
Mom, I tried.

331
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:44,367
For years, I tried to hold it
together.

332
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:46,733
But Mr. Vergara left me hanging.

333
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:51,167
Now I'm drowning in debt.

334
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:53,267
Every month, I don't even know
how we're going to get by.

335
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,700
I'm barely holding on.

336
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:57,267
I feel like I'm about to break.

337
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:01,500
My husband told me the business
was doing well.

338
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:04,633
I left when the operations
started losing money.

339
00:21:04,767 --> 00:21:06,700
I don't know what your husband
told you.

340
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,867
<i>I don't want dad to see me
as a failure.</i>

341
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:13,400
I don't want to hear him say
he was right about me...

342
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:15,700
that I'm worthless,

343
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:19,200
that I'd never amount
to anything.

344
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,867
Have you told Thea?

345
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:23,333
Not yet, Mom.

346
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:27,633
<i>I don't even know
how to tell her.</i>

347
00:21:29,433 --> 00:21:31,200
She might get scared.

348
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:33,000
She might panic.

349
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:36,400
- She might...
- Son, she deserves to know.

350
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:40,200
That company's been down
for a long time.

351
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:43,767
It's hard carrying a problem
like that all by yourself.

352
00:21:43,933 --> 00:21:46,133
You need to tell her.

353
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:48,933
It's better she hears it
from you than from someone else.

354
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:35,833
Hon?

355
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:36,933
What's wrong?

356
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:40,400
Ashley and I were at Lucio's
earlier.

357
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:43,400
And guess who we saw?

358
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:45,833
Mr. Vergara.

359
00:22:45,967 --> 00:22:48,267
Why didn't you even mention

360
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,867
that he already pulled out
of your company?

361
00:22:52,033 --> 00:22:53,600
When are you planning to tell me

362
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:56,400
that our company is about
to shut down?

363
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:57,833
I'm sorry, Hon.

364
00:22:58,167 --> 00:23:00,233
I was going to tell you. But...

365
00:23:01,733 --> 00:23:03,400
I was scared.

366
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:04,867
I didn't want you to worry.

367
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:06,433
I didn't want you to panic.

368
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:11,800
If I had known
what was going on,

369
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:13,700
I could've helped you!

370
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:18,433
You had the nerve to deal
with all of this on your own

371
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:20,067
when you clearly couldn't
handle it!

372
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,100
Enough.

373
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,400
What?

374
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:25,667
This is your pride talking!

375
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:31,400
Instead of asking for help,
you lied to us!

376
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,767
I didn't lie to you.

377
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,900
I was just trying to protect you
from getting hurt.

378
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:38,633
How?

379
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,367
By lying?

380
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,233
I wasn't lying!

381
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:45,033
Hon,

382
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:47,800
I was just waiting for
the right time to tell you.

383
00:23:47,933 --> 00:23:50,733
And when exactly is the right
time, Edward?

384
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:53,067
You always have to be pushed!

385
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:56,200
Because if not, you'll just keep
failing your whole life!

386
00:23:56,367 --> 00:23:57,700
What do you want me to say?

387
00:23:59,667 --> 00:24:01,200
Fine. The company's been
losing money.

388
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:02,400
For a long time.

389
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,533
There were problems
with operations,

390
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:07,333
and I didn't tell you because...

391
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:10,333
because I didn't want
to disappoint you.

392
00:24:12,633 --> 00:24:17,833
I didn't want you thinking
you married a failure.

393
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:23,067
Thea,

394
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:26,900
I did everything I could.

395
00:24:29,433 --> 00:24:32,533
I did everything to fix this.
For us.

396
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:36,100
I just couldn't tell you

397
00:24:36,233 --> 00:24:39,200
because I was scared you'd look
at me like this.

398
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:41,033
Like I'm worthless.

399
00:24:50,167 --> 00:24:52,167
I'm sorry.

400
00:24:54,433 --> 00:24:55,567
I'm sorry.

401
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:02,300
I'm sorry
I'm only telling you now.

402
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:08,267
I couldn't keep my promise
to give you a good life.

403
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:11,800
That we'd succeed. I'm sorry.

404
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:15,133
I'm sorry I failed you
and our child.

405
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:28,133
Our family's future!

406
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:32,233
Our child's future is ruined!

407
00:25:32,367 --> 00:25:32,933
No.

408
00:25:33,067 --> 00:25:35,000
What's your sorry even worth?

409
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:36,367
I'll fix this.

410
00:25:36,533 --> 00:25:38,167
I'll fix it.

411
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:40,167
I'll talk to dad.

412
00:25:40,300 --> 00:25:42,867
And you think that'll solve
anything?

413
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,900
It might just make things worse.

414
00:25:47,767 --> 00:25:49,633
Thea, I'm not lying to anyone
anymore.

415
00:25:49,767 --> 00:25:51,267
I don't want to lie anymore.

416
00:25:52,467 --> 00:25:56,667
The first step to fixing this
is admitting I messed up.

417
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,900
No!

418
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:01,633
I don't trust you anymore!

419
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:06,733
No matter what you do,
it's too late!

420
00:26:09,667 --> 00:26:13,333
This can't be fixed,
so I'll handle it myself!

421
00:26:17,533 --> 00:26:18,600
Thea.

422
00:26:29,700 --> 00:26:31,100
Just leave us alone!

423
00:26:31,233 --> 00:26:33,467
Thea, are you okay?
Who were you talking to?

424
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:38,433
Edward's investors have been
harassing us.

425
00:26:38,667 --> 00:26:42,700
You need to go back to Cebu and
fix this before it gets worse.

426
00:26:42,867 --> 00:26:44,700
I don't think it's safe there.

427
00:26:44,833 --> 00:26:49,233
One of the investors told us
our lives could be in danger.

428
00:26:49,367 --> 00:26:52,467
Ashley shouldn't get dragged
into the mess her mother made.

429
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:56,233
We can protect her better
if she stays with us.

430
00:26:56,367 --> 00:26:59,567
What if something happens
to your granddaughter out there?

431
00:26:59,700 --> 00:27:00,900
Can you live with yourself

432
00:27:01,033 --> 00:27:04,400
knowing you chose your pride
and anger over their lives?

433
00:27:04,533 --> 00:27:05,600
Come on, come with me.

434
00:27:05,733 --> 00:27:10,067
Just a moment. No drama.
No rules.

435
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,700
My granddaughter.

436
00:27:12,833 --> 00:27:15,233
She's still so young.
